ðŸ§  What is Socket.IO?
Socket.IO is a library that lets you build real-time, two-way communication between a client (like a browser) and a server.

Unlike regular HTTP (which is request-response), Socket.IO allows the server and client to send messages at any time â€” like a constant open phone line.

ðŸ§ƒ Simple example:
Imagine a chat app.

Without Socket.IO:
The client has to keep asking the server: â€œAny new messages? Any new messages?â€

With Socket.IO:
The server can just push a new message to the client as soon as it arrives. Fast and efficient!

ðŸ“¦ Uses of Socket.IO
Here are common things you can build using Socket.IO:

âœ… Real-time chat apps
âœ… Live notifications (like â€œsomeone liked your postâ€)
âœ… Multiplayer games
âœ… Live location tracking (like Uber)
âœ… Collaborative apps (like Google Docs)

ðŸ” Now, letâ€™s look at your code:
